SYMPTOM_TEXT: Almost immediately after getting the vaccine, I could hardly breathe, I lost my smell and taste. They recommended I had an x-ray done. I had the x-ray done and it came back with some fluid. I set up an appointment to have a Thoracentesis done. My doctor did it and they retrieved 250CCS. It did not help. The original x-ray showed that I might have developed pneumonia. They finally gave me a prescription for Levaquin and that helped more than anything. I take that after dialysis. I have seen the most effects and results for the better from that medication. I check my oxygen saturation every morning and it is usually at 96-98. But since I got the shot it has not been better than 93. Right now it is 95 and my temperature is 97.8. After the vaccine my temperature did go up to 98.7. They ran a teste for the fluid they took out of my lungs and it came back normal.

I first noticed a pronounced rash and swollen lymph nodes under my left arm within 72 hours of my second vaccination. Within 24 hours of that, I noticed that I also had swollen lymph nodes and a rash under my right arm. The rashes were especially sensitive to the touch. The swelling and redness of the rashes became more pronounced over the following days and weeks, and then they gradually began to subside until they finally resolved themselves about 3 or 4 months after the vaccination. During this time, I corresponded with Dr. via email. He advised me that the rashes were likely a result of the vaccination and that they should resolve over time. However, if they got worse, I was to notify him. Since the rashes eventually resolved themselves, I never had to make any in-person visits to the doctor's office.

I had knee replacement surgery on Feb. 17th and the recovery went well.  I am a healthy, athletic 63 year old male with no prior history of clots nor any known family history. On March 16th, I received the J & J vaccine at the urging of PCP and so I could visit my elderly aunt, who was on hospice care.  Toward the end of May I started to feel very fatigued and was having bilateral joint pain and achy legs which was worse at night when I layed down.  My legs had an incredible ?heaviness? to them, almost like It got so bad that in mid june I contacted my primary doctor and he referred me to the knee surgeon.  The knee surgeon said it wasn?t related to the knee surgery because it was bi-lateral and heaviness is not a common issue related to knee replacement issues.  He thought it might be vascular or nerve or spine related.  I was out of state and flew home to have blood tests done and basically they all retuned normal.  Eventually from insistence by myself, my doctor had mri?s and x-rays done which revealed my spine was not causing the issues with the legs.  During a CT scan for my kidneys, the tech found a pulmonary embolism of my right lower lobe and extending into several segmental arteries.  The doctor is calling it a ?unprovoked? pulmonary embolism. over the last few weeks, I have noticed my eye sight has had moment difficulty focusing long distance and then will clear.  I have better then 20/20 vision.   Throughout my treatment, PCP has repeatedly denied that any of my issues can be related to the JJ vaccine and my doctor said it was ?google? searches that made me think this.  While meeting with a facility Head and Throat surgeon for a parathyroid surgery consult, he urged me to notify the VAERS system because he believed it was all related to J&J vaccine as well.  I am now on blood thinners looking for answers and hoping that some answer can be given as to how this happened by a specialist.
LAB_DATA: july 19 endochronology test Aug 17 MRI Aug 25 Rheumatology Aug 29 Nuerology Sept 4 CT scan Sept 7 Anticoagulation clinic Sept 7 Head and Neck surgery consult Sept 8 Ultrasound Sept 8 CT scan

Patient admitted to COVID floor on 8/25/21 for acute hypoxic respiratory failure secondary to bilateral pneumonia COVID-19. She was initiated on dexamethasone and remdesivir. Pulmonology consulted 8/31 for worsening hypoxemia, on heated high-flow nasal cannula and alternating with noninvasive positive pressure ventilation. On 09/02 patient was transferred to the COVID19 ICU for worsening respiratory status. Patient requested multiple times to delay intubation and maintain on AVAPS. She did have a feeding tube placed and was receiving tube feeds. She essentially became dependent on noninvasive ventilation unable to wean. She did attempt self proning with some improvement in her oxygenation. This morning, patient's oxygen saturations dropped to 60s with increased work of breathing despite noninvasive ventilation and self proning. Discussed with patient again and she was agreeable to being intubated and family agreed. Patient sedated and intubated, unfortunately shortly after intubation patient had a PEA arrest and Code Blue called. See previous note for details. Ultimately, after multiple rounds of CPR, epinephrine, defibrillations without persistent return of spontaneous circulation and approx 35 minutes resuscitation efforts, all resuscitation efforts stopped and time of death called at 08:07am.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I got bit by a dog on my right middle finger on October 24th 2018. Prior to this I was normal. I went to an occupational health center and received a TdaP vaccine that afternoon. The bite was superficial and healed without incident. Clinical signs started within a couple days of vaccination with numbness to my pinky and lateral surface of my vaccinated arm. Then a week later I developed severe neck pain and weakness in my right arm and down my legs.  I went to an ER and was told to just rest. My limbs would fall asleep and felt difficult to move and at times even though i was trying to move my arms, they wouldnt go.  I also developed weakness and couldnt lift things that I was able to in the past.   Around October 30th I developed shifting joint pain (large and small joints) that lasted about 6 months (although progressively improved).  I was placed on ibuprofen from a rheumatologist. Around November 30th I developed trouble breathing and was eventually diagnosed with vocal cord dysfunction. I saw two pulmonologists and was placed on inhaled steroids, spiriva, albuterol, amoxilcillin for 2 weeks and oral steroids for 2 months, none of which led to any improvement. I frequented the ER multiple times but treatments never helped.  I then went to an ENT around march 2020 and was diagnosed with VCD And placed on doxy for 6 weeks in case of a lyme component. It did not help. I developed an enlarged axillary and submandibular lymph node on the right. My right armpit was uncomfortable. About 1.5 years later the joint pain and neurological weakness subsided. The lymph nodes are shrinking as of 9/2021 and my breathing has improved although VCD signs are still present
LAB_DATA: 2019 -normal bloodwork, normal RF and negative for genetic rheumatalogical diseases, negative for tick borne diseases (including lyme, babesia and anaplasmosis, normal pulmonary function testing, normal CT scans of lungs, normal MRI of brain, Vocal cord dysfunction diagnosed via scope at UCONN health.  2020 - Enlarged axillary lymph nodes on ultrasound  2021 - normal mammogram and shrinking axillary lymph nodes

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I obtained the first dose of the Covid 19 Pfizer vaccine on Saturday  August 28 2021 after discovering that I was pregnant the same day.  My blood test was drawn to check my HCG levels on Tuesday August 31st 2021 and Thursday September 2nd 2021 and results showed that pregnancy was progressing normally based on the levels obtained these two days. On Saturday September 4th 2021 I started to bleed (light bleeding, spotting). It happened in the morning  then stopped a bit and it happened again in the afternoon. I experienced light bleeding and spotting again on Sunday September 5th 2021. On Monday September 6th I continued to experience light bleeding during the day but the the flow of blood increased at night.  I contacted my doctor on Monday September 6th she advised me to get another blood test to check my HCG level on Wednesday September 8th 2021. On Tuesday September 7th  the bleeding became heavy like a period. I continued to bleed heavily on Wednesday September 8th 2021. I got my blood test done on Wednesday September 8th 2021 per my doctor's instruction. Today Thursday September 9th 2021 I got my results back and my HCG level dropped to non pregnant level.  I spoke with my doctor's nurse today Thursday September 9th and after she reviewed the HCG number she informed me that I had suffered a miscarriage.  I am still experiencing bleeding today Thursday September 9th 2021.
LAB_DATA: Blood test to check HCG level performed on Wednesday September 8th 2021 due to the bleeding.  Results indicated that I suffered a miscarriage.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 4/13: second moderna dose, felt sort of ?out of it?, a bit tired but no other serious side effects  4/14: still feeling out of it?especially visually now, sort of like my depth perception is off or vision is a little blurry  4/15: start to realize that blurred vision and heartbeat sensation and light flashes and ?vein imprints? are all local to left eye, right eye perfectly normal  4/16: complained about left eye blurriness to coworkers and they said they were experiencing the same thing; chalked it up to possible allergies  4/23: go to doctor for blurry vision. Right eye tests 20/15; left eye 20/25. Unsure of diagnosis but refers me to ophthalmologist  4/28: appointment with ophthalmologist. runs a series of tests including peripheral vision test (normal), OCT, and diagnoses an acute macular lesion; refers me to see a retina specialist the following day  4/29: appointment with specialist runs another series of tests including dye test (normal) and OCT, diagnoses epiretinal membrane/macular pucker. Says surgery is the only way to fix but hesitant to do so as surgery leads to vitreous degeneration and cataracts; since I?m young cataract surgery will make my vision worse than it already is. schedules follow-up for 5/27  5/6: hesitant to say vision is getting worse but I think it might be?definitely not improving. Visually stimulating environments (hardware store, gardens) leave me feeling very dazed and overwhelmed. Constantly tired. Have trouble focusing on things.  5/7: feel like hand-eye coordination is deteriorating?buttering a bagel feels like an unlearned skill  5/12: lots more white/light arcs around edge of vision; also pupil outline in center?  5/16: depth stuff feels much more off; strong imprint of retinal veins upon opening eye after blinking  5/26: more light arc flashes in bottom-left quadrant of FOV when moving eye rapidly  5/27: follow up appointment with specialist said only half-surprising that the ERM has progressed in the month since last visit, vision still not bad enough to rush surgery but will check in in two and a half months? time. said rather unequivocally that he believes it to be a result of the vaccine (no evidence of tear/trauma, pucker is so perfectly symmetrical, looks un organic, etc.) half-joked he might write a paper about me
LAB_DATA: see item 18--OCT showing major, symmetrical macular pucker

SYMPTOM_TEXT: on 8/6 received shot, had arm pain that evening and felt tired. The next day, arm pain was worse and top of arm felt hot and sore to the touch. Continued on Sunday. On 8/9, flu like symptoms and felt really bad. My wrist was starting to feel achy. on 8/11, the flu like symptoms had gone away but had extreme wrist pain, so much so that I couldn't bear weight on it.  on 8/15, I was in a yoga class and couldn't bear any weight on it. I wore a brace for the next few days. The week of 8/19 I started to notice the pain had moved from my wrist up into my forearm. I started experiecing bad headaches that would start at base of my head on the left side. I started to experiencing neck and shoulder pain on the left side of my body. Later into the week, my left side lymph nodes were swollen, i had pain in my ear. I noticed that lying down my left side of my face felt looser, specifically at my mouth, where it felt almost like I was slighty drooling. I have never ever experience any things such as these, and it was all left side dominant. On 8/26, i couldn't stand the wrist pain anymore, so I visited my chiropractor to see if by change i had a broken wrist or something else causing all these problems. I told them about the shot and they said some people feel pain, but not normally 3 weeks later though some RA or autoimmune patients have experience longer term joint pain. I have never been diagnosed with either of those, and again it was only happening on the left side.  THe pain continues into the weekend and following week. on 8/30, I woke up with pain in my shoulder and rotator cuff, to the point where it hurt to lift my arm.  I went to my massage therapist to see if she could work out the body pain. I had my last massage with her in July. At this appointment, she told me my left side felt completely different: my muscles felt ropey, hard, and only on the left side. This was present in my left arm, neck, left pectoral muscles, face, and top of skull. The left side of my skull felt as if it were swollen.  on 8/31, I woke up with a swollen elbow and a not the size of walnut in my inner left elbow . On 9/2, I went to see my gynecologist for a medical procedure (iud replacement) and the nurse couldn't take my blood pressure on the left side due to the pain. She asked if I had a bad blood draw or had injured my arm when she saw the swelling. I told her what happened and she told me I should file a report here because that actually happened to her and she was allergic to the shot. Though i had not told many, no one had my symptoms until I met her. I was supposed to take the second shot but declined due to the fact I was still dealing with issues surrounding the first one and I don't want to do anything that steals any more of my mobility. I still have the swollen elbow, shoulder pain, and lymph nodes  as of 9/9, I finally am seeing improvement in my wrist, being able to bear weight on it once again, but still not back to its normal pre-shot mobility. I started to notice 9/6 - 9/9 that I have had some weird sensations in legs...left knee locking up, sharp pain down the arch of my foot across the pad of my foot, randomnly and sharp pains. Again....all left dominant. I don't know what is wrong: if I am having an allergic reaction or if my shot was messed up. SYMPTOM_TEXT: HOSPITAL ADMISSION SUMMARY; A relatively healthy 51-year-old male who acutely complained of severe pain while he was about to eat dinner with his family at around 4:00 p.m.,  just had 2 bites of carrots when he began having severe abdominal pain described as diffuse and fairly intense. He apparently became diaphoretic and had multiple episodes of vomiting. He profoundly became sick so he was brought to our ER where he initially presented hypoxic and tachypneic. Workups done showed WBC of 17.4, creatinine of 1.36, mild transaminitis and lipase of 40,900. He had undergone CT abdomen which showed findings suggestive of mild pancreatitis centered in the pancreatic head region and an ultrasound which revealed 1.7 cm nonshadowing sessile echogenic nodular focus near the gallbladder which may represent gallbladder polyp versus biliary sludge. He was given 2 L IVF, several doses of fentanyl, Dilaudid and Zofran. Patient was still writhing in pain when I evaluated him. He denies prior history of similar problem and claims he was in his baseline health before the onset of his presenting symptoms. He apparently had a bottle of beer after his routine walk at around 11:00 a.m. to celebrate Memorial day. He is not aware of any hepatic biliary issue and does not drink alcohol regularly (maximum around 6 packs per month). He does have GERD for which he is on PPI. He does not smoke. He is retired from military and currently works for the government. HOSPITAL COURSE- patient presented with intractable abdominal pain and vomiting, found to have acute, mild pancreatitis. Due to lack of improvement a follow up CT of the abdomen was done on 6/4 which showed worsening pancreatic necrosis, developing pseudocyst and superior mesenteric vein thrombosis. On 6/5 he had to be transferred to the ICU for worsening condition. He was eventually intubated and started on dexmedetomidine and furosemide. He remained intubated until 6/8 when he was extubated after he passed spontaneous awakening and spontaneous breathing trial. However his white blood cell continued to climb and remained febrile. At this point vancomycin was started. He was also started on tube feedings. However on the 6/11 he started having significant output from his nasogastric tube. There is question about his ability to absorb medication. After a few days he started showing improvement and general surgery started him on a clear liquid. He continued to improved and he was eventually moved out of ICU to the medical floor on floor on 6/13. However the following day, 6/14, he again had Increased abdominal pain while just on clear liquid diet. A repeat CT abdomen was done which showed increased peripancreatic fluid collection. GI was consulted on 6/15 to evaluate for NJ feeding tube placement. However this was not done until 6/17 due to patient spiking a fever of 101.2 F on 6/16. On his EGD it showed superficial ulceration within the pre-pyloric antrum s/p nasoenteric feeding tube placement. He was again placed on tube feedings. On 6/18 his tube feedings were near goal. However his abdominal pain started to increase again and his abdomen was also noted to be consistently distended. He was also requiring significant amount of IV pain medication. This was discussed with ACS who recommended to get a repeat CT abdomen pelvis. GI also recommended changing his antibiotic to meropenem. Unfortunately he had a reaction to meropenem and after discussion with ID his antibiotic was again changed to Zosyn. His repeat CT in the meantime showed further increase in size and number of pseudocysts. ACS service advised for conservative management and GI discussion. No plan for urgent surgery. IR Service was also consulted to evaluate for cyst drainage but after discussion with ACS they did not go through with the aspiration to avoid fistula formation. At this point the patient was taken of tube feeding and was placed on TPN. The patient finally started having consistent improvement. His WBC trending down and became normal. His NGT was eventually discontinued as well as his antibiotic per GI and ACS recommendation on 6/23. He had a repeat CT abdomen and pelvis on 7/6 which showed no definite pancreatic necrosis and pseudocysts remain unchanged. His nausea managed eventually with scheduled reglan and PRN zofran and for his pain, PRN dilaudid and scheduled ER oxycodone. He is tolerating his TPN and oral meds with sips of water at this point but still couldn't tolerating any food orally. The patient will need to have another CT abdomen and pelvis done with contrast to evaluate the pseudocyst in 4-5 weeks (end of July). He can then be referred to outpatient GI through the VA to determine if he needs aspiration of his pancreatic pseudocyst. This was the recommendation by ACS and GI here in the hospital. FINAL DIAGNOSIS- Acute pancreatitis necrotizing/ Pancreatic pseudocyst secondary to above/  Severe sepsis/ Orthostatic hypotension/ A. Fib/ Mesentric vein thrombosis partial/Acute respiratory failure with hypoxia/ MRSA pneumonia/ Transaminitis/ Ileus: resolved/ Encephalopathy/ Elevated blood sugar:/ Protein-calorie malnutrition, moderate/ Drug rash

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Symptoms: Day 0 - 8/28/2021 Extremely mild injection site pain; Day 1 - 8/29/2021~36 hours post-injection: Acute extreme abdominal distension (bloating), shortness of breath, dizziness, pre-syncope, confusion, lack of concentration, sweating. Took 20mg Diphenhydramine and laid supine followed by nap. Symptoms subsided. Day 2-4 -3-4 daily bouts of dizziness, bloating, shortness of breath, lack of concentration. Eating food worsened bloating. Assumed possible constipation and dosed with Magnesium Citrate. Diarrhea followed, along with assumed dehydration/malnutrition. Began mostly liquid diet (meat broths) along with occasional crackers, grilled chicken, and vegetables like bell peppers, green beans, and potatoes. Day 5 - 9/2/2021***ER visit at 6:30PM 9/2/2021.*** Roughly the same symptoms as Day 1: Acute extreme abdominal distension (bloating), shortness of breath, dizziness, pre-syncope, confusion, lack of concentration, sweating. Tests included: EKG, Chest X-ray, shoulders-to-waist CT scan. Full blood work. All came back normal. IV administered for hydration, vital signs were monitored for 2-3 hours. All normal. Doctor prescribed ondansetron for nausea, which was not present; Day 6 and onward Switched to diet of oatmeal, cereal, bananas, grilled/baked chicken, lightly seasoned ground beef, green beans, yogurt. Symptoms show improvement.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The morning after the first dose i woke up dizzy.  It subsided during the day, but returned that night upon lying down in bed.  This reoccurred every morning and night for well over a month and after the second dose.  It would subside during the day, but i did have periods of lightheadedness during the day.  These still occur every so often.  I had never had this issue before.  After the second dose i had a rash on parts of my arms and legs that i had never experienced before either.  It looked like tiny little bites all clustered but was not any kind of bug bite. None of the spots were severe, but they itched like mad and would appear randomly in different parts of limbs.  This lasted maybe a week or two. I took an over-the-counter allergy pill for a few days and it subsided.  I still get the occasional bump, but they are not as itchy nor do they last as long.  The last thing to happen is the almost chronic joint pain, especially in my hips.  I have worked on my feet for almost 40 years and have never had issues with my hips.  They just ache and this was a sudden onset, not gradual (as would be expected with aging) and is different than mere pain from workload.  This is the most bothersome and my fiance even said he has never heard me complain about the pain as much as i have lately.  I take an Aleve almost everyday, where i used to only take one occasionally for lower back pain.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received the first dose on March 6.  On March 14 I developed a weal on my upper right arm.  It started about the size of a quarter, but very quickly move to 2-3" in diameter, raised, and Itchy.  It initially was treated with Doxycycline. I received the second dose on 3/27.  about 2 weeks after that, the weal returned.  This time it moved the length of my arm over the time of a week.  This time it was treated with antihistamines.  The weals continued around my body on and off, including the bottom of my feet..  I was able to get into a Dermatologist on June 9, who took a  biopsy of my lower right arm.  The results came back 2 weeks later that it was Chronic Urticaria.  On July 3 I suddenly developed Angioedema of the lips, and ended up in ER.  I was treated with intravenous Benadryl, famotidine, and prednisone, and put on famotadine and predisone for the next 2 weeks.  While things went away for a while, the series of Hives started again, and 2 days after my feet swelled, I developed the Angioedema again and was back in ER.  This has continued  throughout the summer, and continues to the current day.  I have had one more ER Visit on 8/28.  I am currently on Zyrtec, Famotidine, montelkast, and Allegra to treat the hives.
LAB_DATA: June 9 Biopsy of left lower arm.
OTHER_MEDS: Tegretol, Omeprozole, Olmestartin Menoxodil, Anastrozole, Xyzal.

Pfizer BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine EUA: COVID-19 case resulting in Hospitalization / Death. Patient received Pfizer Vaccines on 1/14/2021 and 2/2/2021. Patient contacted physician office on 8/9/2021 stating had a positive COVID HOME test on 8/8/2021 with a three day history of sore throat, headache, congestion, coughing also noted to have oxygen level of 81 and fever of 101.9. Patient was retested on 8/10/2021 and was positive. Patient presented to ED on 8/10/2021 with complaints of shortness of breath.  On presentation SpO2 100% on room air without significant tachypnea, but with mild bilateral wheezes. Patient received Imdevimab+casirivimab and was discharged home @ 1645. Patient presented back to ED at 2011 in  respiratory distress with increased work of breathing, accessory muscle use, and transient hypoxia. Noted O2 sats of 74% on room air, and placed on high-flow nasal cannula. Patient improved rapidly overnight coming down to just 2 L NC by the following morning. Patient stated she felt better as well denying SOB, fevers or chills but reporting some cough. Patient O2 needs had decreased to 4 L on ambulation by 8/13. She was discharged on home with home O2 on 8/13. She was prescribed dexamethasone to complete a total of 10 days of therapy for COVID and cefdinir to complete 5 days of therapy for suspected overlying bacterial PNA. Patient presented to ED on 8/14/2021 due to shortness of breath. She was  transferred to ICU 8/15 due to acute hypoxic respiratory failure due to COVID-19 pneumonia and found to have secondary bacterial pna.  Patient returned to the floor in hosptial but subsequently bounced back to the ICU 8/25 and intubated 8/26.  Patient continued to deteriorate and palliative care was consulted.  8/31 decision was made by family to pursue DNR/AND.  Patient passed away peacefully at 8:54PM on 8/31/2021.
LAB_DATA: Positive COVID test on 8/10/2021 using the Roche LIAT SARS assay platform using PCR or equivalent nucleic acid amplification technology.

Janssen COVID-19 Vaccine EUA: COVID-19 case resulting in Hospitalization / Death. Patient received Janssen Vaccine on 3/11/2021. Presented to ED on 8/25/2021 with a 9-10 day history of coughing, fevers, diarrhea, fatigue, hypoxia, myalgiam and chills. She was started on Dexamethasone on 8/26 and continued this through her hospital course.  Eventually her oxygen requirements escalated and she required intubation on 8/27/21 due to persistent significant hypoxia despite maximum non-invasive interventions. A trialysis catheter was also placed for her and nephrology was consulted due to urgent need for dialysis as her kidney function continued to deteriorate since admission. Renal ultrasound did not show any hydronephrosis or obstructive processes.  On 8/27 she had 3L removed via HD. She required paralytics, sedation, and pain control while on the ventilator. On 8/27/21, her code status was changed to DNAR/COT. Eventually, she developed septic shock and was found later to be bacteremic (GPC in clusters) with a positive MRSA PCR nares. The culture did not have a final result by the time of her passing. She was started on broad spectrum antibiotics on 8/30 at the time of her becoming more septic.  On 8/31, the patient's MAPs and oxygen saturations continued to decrease despite maximal therapy (including four vasopressors). The patient passed away at 0630 on 8/31/21.

Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine EUA  Patient came to vaccine clinic with her family member and received J&J vaccine at 1245. I took her to the back room to observe her for 30 minutes.  She reported history of anaphylaxis to Pfizer in January of 2021. I took her vitals at 1253. BP 119/64; HR 96, SpO2 97 % on RA.    At 1301 she reported difficulty breathing. I administered 3 mg of Epi via left lateral thigh. Vitals after first dose of Epi was: BP 120/63; HR 91, SpO2 99% on 6 liters via nasal cannula. Patient reported that her breathing was getting better.    At 1310 patient stated that she was having difficulty swallowing her saliva. I administered 50 mg IM Benadryl.    I called Dr.and reported patient had Anaphylaxis and was not improving. Dr. and his team came right away. Nurse called urgent care. Nurse called emergency services.    At 1315 second dose of Epi was given. Vital signs at 1318 were BP 92/73; HR 111, SpO2 100% on 6 liters via nasal cannula. She was shivering and coughing out phlegm. Silver blanket was applied to keep patient warm.   At 1320 the third dose of Epi was given and patient reported some relief.    Paramedics came around 1325. Patient BP was 160/100. Patient had two episodes of nausea and vomiting. She was taken to Medical Center via ambulance.   Nurse  manager was notified.
OTHER_MEDS: During the code the patient's family member stated that she used an inhaler. She has a history of Asthma and bronchitis.
PRIOR_VAX: Anaphylaxis to Pfizer in January 2021
ALLERGIES: Penicillin, Amoxicillin, Toradol, Morphine, Ibuprophen, Pfizer

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On 1/13/2021, I received my first dose of the Moderna vaccine. On1/23/2021, I developed a rash at the injection site, which went away within 10 days. On 2/13/2021, I received the second dose. On about 2/20/2021, I developed a rash over various parts of my body. They look like spider bites and are pimple-like bumps filled with clear liquid. It looked like acne, but the bumps had no pus. The bumps would pop up from nowhere in random places. Every part of my body has been affected at some point, save for the palms of my hands, the soles of my feet, and my genital area. My face has mostly been unaffected, though I have had a few bumps on my nose. I went to my PCP, and I was referred to a dermatologist. The dermatologist gave me steroidal cream. The bumps would disappear after a few days when I put the cream on them. To this day, I still have bumps that pop up, and I treat them with the cream the dermatologist gave me.

When I took the medicine I was very energetic and bouncing on the sofa. I stopped taking it because coming down off worsened the anxiety attacks greatly. Later that week I was given a script for Zoloft but also couldn?t take it because it made my anxiety worse. On Sunday sept 5 I went back to the Er for vertigo, numbness in my left arm, blurred vision, head pressure, and ringing in my ears. I had more tests done and all came back negative. Later that night I went back in because the vertigo, blurred vision, and head pressure was too much. I was kept for observations and given an MRI to rule out any other possible causes. All came back fine. The anxiety attacks are beginning to dissipate all together but I am still experiencing vertigo.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The day of vaccine I was very tired. The next day I felt fine but by dinner time just felt like I was getting a cold. The fever and body aches began. By Monday the 2nd I began to feel as if I had a bad head cold. I had a fever and could barely move. By Thursday the 5th I was very ill and the coughing had begun. I saw the doctor who believed it was merely bronchitis. By Monday the 9th the cough had been so bad, even with medication, I had pulled all muscles in my back and torn something in my stomach. I had called the doctor again on the 11th and my doctor's associate had then given me a second dose of a different antibiotic. She also ordered a chest X-ray which  she said "showed my lungs cloudy but did not see pneumonia". I felt a bit better after 3 days of the new antibiotics. To date I am still coughing but not what I had suffered during the 3 weeks of suffering. The week after getting vaccinated, I was not able to walk, eat, drink normally, I had headaches, I had a fever, I was delusional. It felt like I was hit by a truck. And then it slowly got better and I felt absolutely fine. After getting vaccinated, I started going outside a bit more, and walking more, and that is when I realized that my stamina had completely decreased. Then, in late May, I was at the mall walking and my heart skyrocketed. I had severe heart palpitations, chest pain, and extremely weird tachycardic beats. I was diagnosed with sinus arrhythmia and benign not common heart palpitations that lasted very little. This was completely different. If I had to estimate it would be close to The 200s. I called EMS And they had to walk me out to where my ride walked me back to the car. Ever since that day my body has completely changed. I am constantly exhausted, exhausted actually is an understatement. The immediate day after my heart was still seemingly tachycardic, I had chest pains, my heartfelt week, it felt like my ribs and my chest cavity were breaking, I could not walk or get up from bed or even shift positions while I was sleeping without my heart rate skyrocketing and the blood rushing from my head and feeling lightheaded and dizzy. Psychologically I was also not my best. My body not working the way it needs to give me extreme anxiety, and I could not be alone for the longest time. It started to get better but four months later I still have lingering symptoms. I had Covid back in Christmas of 2020 but it felt like allergies and we did not have a severe effect on me it seemed. The vaccination and how it reeked havoc on my body has seemed worse than the actual disease. Symptoms I have now is consistent breathlessness which worsens on some days and is better on others, but it is always there. I can?t run or walk fast without my body seeming like it has to catch up with me. I get chest pains I still get heart palpitations and sometimes my heart races for no reason at all and my resting heart rate is about 110 generally. And the worst one of all is I feel this constant pressure under my rib cage and above my belly button that never goes away and it was not there before. I have gone to two cardiologists Since then, my primary care doctor multiple times, made multiple ER visits, I?ve gone to a pulmonologist, and I?ve gone to a gastroenterologist and did an endoscopy. Every single doctor I go to says there?s nothing wrong with my body. I am in the mist of getting a second opinion for a pulmonologist and a check up on my gallbladder but every test consistently comes back negative. I I have always been around tons of people, been around crowds, and have loved exploring in the past. Now I have developed severe social anxiety where I can?t even drive through cities without someone with me or walk down the street. I have become hyper sensitive to loud noises, vibrant displays, and I prefer the silence. And for weeks I could not leave my house and I was afraid I was agoraphobic. All in all I feel like a completely different person than I was before getting the vaccine. No one knows what is going on with me and I can?t often articulate or verbalize the experience that I?m dealing with. The worst part of it all is the breathlessness part and the feeling of my body deconditioning from the vaccine. Some days it feels like my lungs are full of hot air but to no avail.
LAB_DATA: Every single one. X-rays, blood tests, general ER checks, etc. And that is just general doctors. All negative. Endoscopy, negative. Cardiogram, negative. Pulmonologist review, negative (thought it was Asthma so was prescribed three different inhalers).
PRIOR_VAX: Flu shot, 17 years ago

On the morning of  02 March 2021 I started to experience pain and inflammation on the right upper check, next, arm, back, and abdomen side of my body.   This pain occurred for 2 weeks and subsided for a week. After a week the pain appeared again in the same positions.   At the time due to the pandemic, I could not see receive an appointment with my primary care physician. On 21 April 2021, 5:40 P.M.  I visited Urgent Care with Doctor C  at Clinic.   The results of the X-Ray near my neck/spinal area/chest were normal. Following the visit, my primary physician Doctor O. referred me to a neurologist. On 04 May 2021, 3:45 P.M., I visited Doctor A at the Clinic.  Doctor A. assessed my condition and ordered an MRI. On 24 May 2021 at 3:50 P.M., I visited the Radiology Clinic. There they conducted the MRI for about an hour.   Three days later 27 May 2021, 4:30 P.M. I had a follow-up appointment with my neurologist, Doctor A. She confirmed I had a pinched nerve originating on the right side of my neck with a substantial amount of inflammation and degeneration throughout the upper part of my body.   On 26 August at 2P.M. I underwent a steroid/cortisone injection procedure with Doctor H. Imaging.  There he conducted a CT scan and administered a cortisone/steroid injection. Afterward within minutes my pain and inflammation were gone. This was temporary.  Afterward, 2 days up to a week later my pain and inflammation returned at 50% remaining. As of 09 September 2021, my pain and inflammation are at 25% remaining. Currently, I am in the process of completing and turning in a self-assessment to the radiology department to determine if I should undergo a 2nd steroid/cortisone injection in hopes to further reduce the inflammation/pain.   On 08 September 2021, at 2:20 P.M. I visited my primary physician Doctor O. to provide an update and overview of my prognosis and condition in the past 6 months In order to assess follow-up care. Recommendations were to possibly undergo a 2nd Cortisone/Steroid injection, continue physical therapy, take muscle relaxers, and ibuprofen in hopes of continuing to reduce the inflammation down to 100%. SYMPTOM_TEXT: This is from the second shot. The first shot was a little over 3 weeks prior. Nothing happened other than a slightly sore arm. The second vaccination was much worse. The day of, arm was just sore. I rubbed it, applied cold and warm compress, the nurse there said if I was in pain to take Tylenol or motrin, so thats what I did. The next day I couldn't move. A friend had to take my kids to school because I could not get off the sofa. I had a 103.8 fever, I couldn't see, my head was pounding, the room was spinning, and  couldn't swallow. I took Tylenol and drank a lot of water. I couldn't eat anything. It lasted all day and the next day I had the same all over body aches, headache, felt exhausted but no fever. Ever since then my period has been completely out of wack. I had it in June, but completely missed July, August was only here for 2 days and was very light, now I am in September and its also not here. I have taken multiple pregnancy tests and not pregnant, I also have my tubes tied. I have also have had recurring headaches, stomach pain, abdominal pain, abdominal burning, felt like my skin was on fire but no rash, my chest feels tight and I'm forgetting things. I've also been having terrible back pain and neck stiffness. I have never had any of these symptoms before. My doctor doesn't know what is the cause. They did blood work and just said its probably stress from moving from the states to overseas. But i was having these symptoms before I moved. No one is taking me seriously and im tired of having pain.
LAB_DATA: I went to the doctor in July 2021 and he thought I was just constipated and gave me miralax. After about 30 minutes of taking miralax I couldnt get off the toilet due to having terrible abdominal pain and severe diarrhea. I stopped taking it after that.  I saw a doctor a week later again, she did a pap smear and breast examination. Everything came back normal. They did full blood work and nothing was wrong and couldnt find anything.  The day after I started bleeding, doctor said it was my long overdue period. it lasted two days with heavy blood clots. the blood itself wasnt a lot, which isnt normal.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pfizer BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine EUA: COVID-19 case resulting in Hospitalization / Death. Patient received Pfizer Vaccine on 05/06/2021 and 06/03/2021. Patient presents to ER on 8/6/2021 referred directly from outpatient clinic with chief complaint of fever, chills, chest pain and dyspnea times 3 days. He was admitted to medical floor 08/06/2021 for acute hypoxemic respiratory failure secondary to COVID pneumonia requiring 2 L supplemental oxygen via nasal cannula. Patient received remdesivir, ceftriaxone, Bactrim and Baricitinib. On 08/10, oxygen demand increased from 7 L nasal cannula to high-flow nasal cannula 40 L 40% FiO2. When I had the vaccine, the next day, I was a little sore at the injection site and was very tired. About a month or so later, I had a little rash on the back of my neck and on my right side. I had hives on my legs arm and stomach. I didn't know the rash had moved down my back to the top of my butt, down my legs, my shoulders up into my hair and in my groin (on the skin) I went to the doctor who sent me for blood work. The blood work showed I had ANA. I was then sent to a rheumatologist. They said they did not find anything conclusive. They said I had nothing to worry about, it was not any underlying condition. My PCP sent me to a dermatologist that gave me something topical. It had aluminum in it, and I do not use aluminum, so I did not use it. I was sent to another dermatologist who did a biopsy of the rash. They couldn't figure out what it was. My PCP sent me for more blood work which came back with nothing again. I was tested for Lyme disease which was negative. I was told to take prednisone, but I did not take it because I was determined to be highly sensitive to pharmaceuticals and drugs. I also tried Benadryl at one point which gave slight relief. I was given a cream which I used, and it helped for 15-20 mins. I used some natural remedies such as plantain and yaro paste as well as calendula flower which heled the most. I have also stopped eating red meat. I went to an allergist where I was tested, and nothing was different. I also stopped my blood pressure medication. When I did, my heart started doing something different. I wore a heart monitor, and I was told I might have a heart murmur but nothing to worry about. I also had a stress test done which I did well on. I haven't taken any medication or the past months now. I do still have some hives but not as much as initially. This has been traumatizing for me because I am getting older and I am afraid of taking medication. Also, the rash lasting this long has affected my quality of life severely. I also have pictures of the rash and hives if needed.
LAB_DATA: Stress test; Allergy; Blood work; Determined I was highly sensitive to pharmaceuticals and drugs.
OTHER_MEDS: Losartan; Vitamin C; Vitamin D; Calcium
HISTORY: High blood pressure (under control, not on medication).
ALLERGIES: Highly sensitive to drugs and pharmaceuticals, cats, dust, mold (recent testing).

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Began having severe itching and cracking of skin in the vulva and perianal area. I assumed was possibly bacterial vaginosis. I went to my regular doctor's office gave me antibiotics and told me that if it didn't get better to go see my OB/GYN.  It did not get better, so I made an appointment with my OB/GYN.  He said this is what I think that it is, but let me look to verify. Upon examination he said yes it is Lichen Sclerosus.  It is an autoimmune disease.  It is a lifelong chronic skin condition.  It usually effects pre-pubescent and post-menopausal women, which I am neither. The clobetasol propionate has helped to some degree, but I'm trying to limit the use due to the fact that it is a steroid, and it causes my blood sugar to increase.  I haven't made it to my regular doctor yet to discuss how to handle my diabetes with the use of the cream. Per a tele appointment 8/10/21,  Dr. said if I was still having issues I needed to come back in. I haven't scheduled to  go back to the OB/GYN because I know it will result in having to have a biopsy done of my genitals.   And who wants to do that???
OTHER_MEDS: Lantus, levothryoxine, benazepril-hydrochlorothiazide, rosuvastatin, metformin ER, ozempic, escitalopram, carvedilol, procardia

SYMPTOM_TEXT: vaccine expired in fridge
Severe chest pain for about 2 hours.

It felt like the flu shot, tender but not bothersome. Close to the 15 minutes I started feeling like  a pulling string feeling from my upper shoulder going up towards my neck. I let them know about it and they said to move it around. I was already moving it and massaging my arm. They told me to apply ice on it. They checked on me later and I stayed there for a little over an hour. Then I don't know if its because I was nervous or what but I felt hyper. The whole time before getting the vaccine I was talking a lot and after getting the vaccine I continued to talk a lot instead of feeling down. I continued to ice it. It felt like I was on caffeine. Finally I felt fine. I did not really have any pain or discomfort for the rest of the day. At 3 am in the morning I noticed the pain but I thought it was a dream. I was moaning and turning until I realized it was not a dream. I was having really severe aches and pain deep in my armpit. I did not take any medication so I went back to sleep. The first day I took Tylenol.  After the 3 am episode I was good for pretty much until early afternoon. When I got home I was eating my food and it felt like I was starting to get the pain again. I just iced it again and I was fine. Then, when the vsafe check in came in at around 2:30 that's when things changed. I went to the bathroom and I looked in the mirror and I noticed a little bulge in between my chest and arm. As I raised my arm I noticed a pulling sensation and it was hard to stretch. At this point I would be on the 24 hour mark. I freaked out. Its kind of a significant swelling. Earlier that day I did not notice any swelling. There was some discoloration in my skin. It was like an oval rectangular shape. The tissue was really soft and squishy. At that point I did take Ibuprofen. I just continued to iced it because I continued with the discomfort. The second day, the injection site did feel tender and sore as well. By the 4th day I did not feel anything. No pain. It was absolutely gone. The discoloration was gone. A week later after getting the vaccine its when I first had an episode when my heart was doing something weird, like palpitations and I had an anxiety attack. I breathe through it. I felt like I got through it. My blood pressure and pulse were high. 3 or 4 days after the second week I had another situation, worse than the first time. I was asleep and I woke up out of my sleep and I was feeling weird, my heart was doing the same weird thing. It reminded me when I got Covid. I started feeling shortness of breath. I immediately checked my blood pressure and oxygen. The readings were super high. I was feeling like I was going to go unconscious. I called 911 because I was by myself and my daughter. They came home and they evaluated me. My blood pressure had come down. They said they did not see any heart situation going on but that does not mean there is not something going on. They wanted me to go to the hospital but I could not go because I had to take care of my daughter. I told them I would call if necessary. I tried to calm myself with teas and meditations. Currently I find myself tired and wanting to sleep a lot. I am still dealing with anxiety. A week and a half after I called the doctor because I was outside and I had a feeling of a stabbing needle. I looked at my arm and there was no bump or anything but my vein was bulged out. I felt like all my veins were popping out. They said it was like a spasm.
6 months pregnant, due December 2021. Experienced dizziness, nausea, vomiting, loss of balance, needed help walking.
LAB_DATA: Doctor diagnosed it as labyrinthitis, prescribed oral steroids, Zofran, and Flonase. Took 7 days to recover once medicine was introduced
PRIOR_VAX: Guillain-Barr, Flu Shot, 18 months

After 2 weeks, I'm back to normal. I have totally recovered.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I did not know I was pregnant at the time I received the first dose. They sent me directly to OB triage on 07/18/2021. I got something called HELLP syndrome and I had extremely high blood pressure, my platelets dropped very low, I had protein in my urine. I was in the hospital for a couple of days because my baby was born at 26 weeks. I had to be put on magnesium sulfate. I had to have an emergency c- section. My blood pressure remains elevated 7 weeks postpartum and I still have swelling in my legs. I still remain on blood pressure medications.  It is rare for symptoms to persist these long after delivery and I still have edema and high blood pressure.   Pregnancy history- first baby, I was considered  a high risk pregnancy, I had to go to the OB pretty often. I was supposed to be due at 35 weeks but my baby was born at 26. Otherwise it was pretty unremarkable, a lot of ultrasounds which were normal.  My baby's weight was 850 grams

SYMPTOM_TEXT: During the day of the vaccine, I was fine except a little bit tired. At night, in bed, I couldn't move at all - neither left or right, hand or feet or legs - everything was hurting me. I couldn't move. In the morning, I took Tylenol after calling my brother who is a doctor - and he said to take every six hours for three days. It helped get the pain away. August 17th, I start to cough a little bit and went to the doctor, and he did a Rapid test (PCR) and it was negative result - (doctor's office). He gave something for my cough. He gave me steroids - Cortisone - for five days. After I finished that pack, I had a headache at night and couldn't sleep due to it and I took a Tylenol. I couldn't sleep. During the day, I was coughing - a little one that comes and goes. There was nothing like mucus coming out (It wasn't phlegm being coughed up - it felt like water coming out when I cough something up). During the night, again, around 03:00 am and I had a headache again and couldn't sleep again due to it. Thursday, I was supposed to do a PCR, but I didn't have time and that night I didn't have headache. Friday, I did go back and re-did the COVID test (Urgent Care on), and it tested positive. At that time, I just had a little cough but no headache anymore. My granddaughter, who goes to day care, and who I babysit, had started to cough before I did. My doctor did give me a medicine to take after I had the positive result for COVID - I can't remember the name of it but like the first pack of Cortisone but not the same.  Wednesday (the following Wednesday after the positive test), I tested again, and it was negative for COVID (at the Urgent Care). Presently, sometimes when I smell something - like onion or pepper - I feel like I want to cough again - a little hack. My left part of my nose - I had surgery there - so every time they swab (for the COVID test) it hurts so bad. I don't have the headache anymore that I had in the nights.
LAB_DATA: COVID tests - 2 negative and one positive

During my first dose,  3 weeks prior to this event, I experienced high fevers (up to 104 degrees), chills, night sweats, joint pain, and I also started menstruating 2 weeks postpartum. At the time I also noticed a drop in my milk supply, and a regression in my baby's ability to latch (unsure if this is related to the vaccination event, but it coincided). During my second dose, date of this reported event I experienced milder symptoms of the same type: fever (up to 103 degrees), night sweats, milder joint pain, and again began to have spontaneous vaginal bleeding similar to a period. I have not discharged any more lochea and believe that the vaccine has again triggered a very distinct and period like vaginal bleeding. My milk supply has again seemed to drop post the second dose. I believe the vaginal bleeding and milk supply decrease are related; the vaccine leading to some sort of hormonal change causing vaginal bleeding or menstruation which can impact milk supply. All of the other symptoms with the exception of milk supply increase resolved themselves within 24-36 hours respectively and did not have lingering effects.
CUR_ILL: None- delivered healthy full term baby 5 weeks prior.

On June 14th, 2021, I got my first Covid-19 Moderna Vaccination. Within a few hours of receiving the vaccination, I developed a significant itch on my left hand. The itching continued on into the night with no relief. Upon arising the next morning I developed a severe outbreak of the hives. I called the doctor and he prescribed Benadryl which gave me some relief. The severity of the hives continued over the next two weeks without significant change. It took me a month before I was completely free of the outbreaks. On August 12th I had another outbreak in three locations, but it lasted only one day without treatment.  In addition, I experienced numbness in my feet following the shot, but I was so focused on ridding myself of the hives the numbness did not concern me until it became so prominent that my feet began to feel like they were weighted down and felt very heavy. I consulted with three doctors over the next three months to determine if there could be any other explanation other than the Moderna Vaccine. Unfortunately, none of the doctors could give me an alternative explanation for the numbness. Although the numbness continues as I complete this report, I have sensed that there has been a slight improvement over the past week.
LAB_DATA: 8/9/21 - Podiatrist - Dr. examined feet and confirmed numbness. 8/17/21 - Consulted with Dr. spine specialist. 8/27/21 - Received and MRI ordered by Dr. 9/9/21 - Follow up consultation with Dr.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Later that night after the vaccine I was really tired. My arm was really sore. I woke up later that night with a pounding headache causing me to sleep all day. I went back to bed and sleep all day the next day and night. 8/21, I noticed eczema had covered most of my right side and it got really itchy on the various places down the right side of my body. This progressed over the next couple of weeks. I felt ok for the next few days but by Wed I was back down and feeling really bad and severely nauseous.   By that Thursday I beginning feeling a little better, but the itchiness and eczema continued to get worse.   On 9/2 I reached out to my PCP and was advised the COVID shot had triggered an immune reaction and caused a lot of inflammation in my body and prescribed a steroid to help.   I was really tired and couldn't sleep.  Was really sweaty at night, but  I take my last dose of the steroid today so hopefully all symptoms will resolves soon, but I am feeling better and no itchiness just left with a lot of scars from the eczema.

Adverse reaction to covid vaccine sent o ED First immunization 12/30/2020 Pfizer Second immunization 8/25/2021 Pfizer (admit to ED 8/25 0948, discharged from ED 1416)  Pt came in for 2nd Pfizer vaccine where she reported her first dose (back in December 2020) caused "a hot tingly feeling going from the injection site, which happened 3 different times and then started sweating and threw up twice." Pt was sent to the ER after 1st dose and continued to have episodes of tingling and vomiting on and off for 5 days. Pt reported extremely dry mouth each time. Pt reports seeing cardiologist and allergist, both of which found no issues with pt health or vaccine. Both providers gave pt okay to get 2nd dose. Pt received 2nd dose at 8:56AM on 8/25/21 and within 5 minutes reported the tingling sensation again. Pt was given 25 mg liquid diphenhydramine in case of allergy, but reported no other symptoms. Pt sat in waiting area for around 45 minutes and had 3 episodes of tingling that were getting longer with each episode. Pts blood pressure was taken twice (~162/88 and ~152/80), but patient reports she was nervous and anxious which was playing a role in high BP. Pt was sent to ER for further monitoring.   Patient is a 58 y.o. female presents to ED for a possible allergic reaction to the Pfizer COVID vaccine. Pt explains that she received the second dose of the vaccine around 0900 today. Afterwards, pt began having whole body tingling and sweating. Pt reports a similar reaction during her first dose of the vaccine in December 2020. Pt was told to come to ED for further evaluation. Pt has already taken an antihistamine before coming to ED.    Patient denies F/C, N/V, CP, dyspnea.    Date/Time: 8/25/2021/9:53 AM   Attending Attestation: The documentation was recorded by acting as scribe in my presence at the time of the encounter and accurately reflects the service I personally performed.  Vaccine reaction, initial encounter Diagnosis management comments: Patient seen and evaluated by Doctor and care followed by PAC.  Patient with past medical history of MI reports for evaluation neuropathy following 2nd dose of COVID vaccine.  Patient states she had her initial vaccine in December 2020.  Following that dose she experienced intermittent burning/whole-body tingling described as being of her head radiating to her toes.  She was seen at multiple ERs and was told she was having vasovagal response.  Symptoms resolved after several days.  She was told prior to 2nd dose to self medicate with antihistamines and complied.  She reported for her 2nd dose this am at 9.  She reports similar burning sensation that began almost immediately after injection; she was told to report to ED for further evaluation.  Patient states the sensation begins at her head and radiates door her feet and is described as a burning/tingling sensation.  She also reports associated dry mouth that was similar to previous injection and body aches beginning in her lower back.  Denies any previous illness, fever, chills, chest pressure, palpitations, shortness of breath, difficulty swallowing, headache, vision changes, injection site reaction, rashes, or any other associated weakness.  Physical exam reveals no focal neurological deficits.  Will further evaluate with EKG, CBC, TSH, magnesium, CMP.   Laboratory evaluation unremarkable.  EKG with normal sinus rhythm.  After initial episode, Patient continues to have no complaints while in the ED for observation upon re-evaluation.  Discussed side effects and return precautions at length with patient.  She will continue Benadryl for the next 24-48 hours and may take Tylenol/ibuprofen for any body aches that may arise.  Patient will follow-up with primary care provider or return to local ED for any new concerns as discussed including chest pain, shortness of breath, difficulty swallowing.

Given epi 0.3mg- unfortunately this was given IV not IM. She developed emesis, improved after zofran and suctioning, was able to protect her airway through this episode. Work of breathing worsened and lungs now severely diminished. Sats still 100%.  Decision made to intubate, which was done successfully as below, after which she was admitted to the ICU." Extubated 9/9 per chart review but remains in hospital.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Vaccinated patient admitted for COVID Admit 8/28/2021, discharge 9/2/2021 to home  Event Description: Pt received COVID-19 vaccine and tested positive for COVID. This is just to report that pt got the vaccine  Date of Positive COVID test and admission 8/28 Moderna Vaccine Date 1/28/2021 Left Deltoid-Lot 007M20A-location unknown-Moderna Date 3/4/2021 Left Deltoid- lot 003A21A-Location unknown -Moderna Monitoring: Pt was started on Remdesivir and Dexamthasone    Reason for consult: Hypertension urgency, COVID-19 PNA Assessment/Recommendations: Admit to inpatient    History Of Present Illness Patient is a 79 y.o. female with PMH of breast cancer not actively on chemo, PE on eliquis, diabetes who presented to the hospital for cough and chest pains.    She notes that she started to have significant coughing spells on Thursday night and has not been able to sleep well. She denies active shortness of breath or dyspnea on exertion. She presented to the ED today due to have right sided chest pain that is pronounced with coughing spells. She has been having productive cough with clear sputum. She noted she has been feeling fatigue since Thursday as well. No reported fever.  No apparent sick contacts but thinks that her daughter is working in school may have passed around the virus. She has completed receiving the vaccine in 3/2021.    She was evaluated in the ED and was found to be + covid. She was also noted to be hypertensive which she reports that she has not been taking her medication in the last 2-3 days. Notably, she was not hypoxic on presentation but was found to be hypoxic around 89% on RA after arrival to hospital.   Social History She reports that she has quit smoking. She has never used smokeless tobacco. She reports that she does not drink alcohol and does not use drugs.  Acute hypoxic respiratory failure  COVID-19 PNA - Noted to be symptomatic around 3 days ago and tested positive for COVID-19 today. Initially did not appear to be hypoxic but was found to be in frequent desaturations to the high 80s on RA on arrival hospital. X-ray supportive of bilateral infiltrates.  - will add inflammatory markers and trend - Start decadron and remdesivir - Supplement 2 L NC to titrate for SPO2 > 90% - Hold abx as low suspicion for co-infection. - No indication for monoclonal ab now.  - Start tessalon pearls for cough, ibuprofen for chest pain as needed    Hypertension urgency  - Noted to have significant BP elevation to 220 mmHg SBP, patient asymptomatic, no end-organ damage - Has been off home meds in the past 3 days. Immediately during and after receiving the Janssen shot in my upper left arm, I felt a burning sensation that radiated outwards from the point of entrance of the needle to my whole upper left arm (about the size of my right hand holding my upper arm). This burning sensation occurred for about 15 minutes after the shot and then stopped. After coming home about an hour after the shot, I had swelling and felt pain in my left arm radiating from the point of the shot down into my fingers which I had expected as a common side effect. However, about 30 minutes after that my left hand began to tremble uncontrollably and was extremely weak. The only time my left hand has trembled and had been so weak was after my work related accident and at the beginning of physical therapy for both of my hands (I had weakness in the right hand too, but regained 80% of its strength in my right hand and about 50 to 60% of strength in my left due to 5 years of physical therapy). Prior to this vaccine both my hands were pain free and did not have severe nor mild trembling and I only had mild trembling in my left hand when there were severe rains or if I overexerted my left hand while crocheting, knitting, or typing of which I have not done any for several months now. Also I had terrible pains down my legs and back during the night which resulted in cold sweat throughout my entire body for 2 hours. Once again I do experience painful cold sweats but only during severe weather (rain or extreme cold) or when I have overexerted myself (i.e. walked too much, sat for more than 30 minutes, or stood up for more than 15 minutes).  My nerves in my legs, back, arms, basically throughout my entire body felt like they were on fire and throbbing. I had to just grit my teeth and let my tears run down my face until the pain stopped. I couldn?t move to get up, shift positions, sit, or anything else. My daughter checked to see if I had a fever and I was 98.0 F, so no fever. All this was nerve pain. It was horrible, I haven't had nerve pain throughout my whole entire body before, but I know what it feels like to have nerve pain in my legs and back and left arm/hand, and this felt like that but worse because I couldn?t move. I don?t know if it was this bad because I had  pre-existing nerve damage in my lower back, legs, hands/wrists, and left arm, but it was the worst feeling and experience with pain that I have ever had (and I had 4 children naturally). Other than the nerve pains I had a severe headache and was extremely tired. Thankfully I am feeling better today, September 10th, 2021. I no longer have any pain in my arm, no headaches, nor tiredness. However, I still have trembling albeit a mild trembling, hopefully the trembling will also stop. Now I am back to my normal unbearable lower back, sciatica, and knee pains of which are very hard on me physically to begin with. Hopefully my trembling will stop and go back to what I was used to and that my experience can help with future patients vaccinated with this COVID 19 vaccine who have disabilities due to injuries and or nerve damage.
OTHER_MEDS: Vitamins D, C, B complex, and A, Saccharomyces 10B, Cetirizine Hydrochloride, Loratadine, Iron, Ibuprofen, and Naprosin.
HISTORY: Permanent disability for lower back and both knees due to work related accident (slip and fall) in January 2011 (over 10 years. My injuries from said accident were my lower back (herniated disks), both knees (torn menisci and ACLs plus no cartilage and bone fragments), both hands and wrists (mild carpal tunnel), and a broken radial head of my left elbow which resulted in permanent mild nerve damage from my elbow to fingers. I had broken the radical head of my elbow and had 5 years of physical therapy to help reduce the weakness and pain and to reduce the occurrences of trembling. Now I only have mild trembling in my left hand when it rains severely or if I have overused my left hand when I am crocheting/knitting or typing on laptop and I have not crocheted nor knitted anything in the last 10 months ( last project was Christmas gift) and this is the first time since June that I have typed on a laptop and that was for remote schooling with my 7 years old daughter. Thus I have not had any trembling mild or otherwise prior to getting vaccinated. The only issues I had prior to this vaccine were pain related due to my injuries to my lower back, knees, left elbow to hand, and right hand. My normal pain level without any pain medicines daily is a 7 and during bad weather it?s a 10, with pain medicine its a 4-5 daily.
ALLERGIES: Dust (indoors and outdoors), latex, glycerine/glycerin/glycerol (all derived forms: animal based, plant based, and synthetic chemically made).

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Client received Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine. A couple minutes after injection, client reported feeling warm and removed his sweatshirt. A few minutes after that, about 5 minutes after injection, he appeared pale and then lost consciousness. He remained upright in the chair with support and did not sustain any injuries. He was unconscious for about 1 minute, with slight jerking movements prior to regaining consciousness. He was moved to an exam table to lay down, ice packs applied to neck and cheek, and drank a few sips of Sprite. He experienced trembling in his left leg and hands and arms, which subsided after 5-10 minutes. He reported some pain on the inside of his left cheek, possibly from biting his cheek during the jerking movements. No blood or significant injury was observed in that area. After 10-15 minutes, he was stable enough to sit, and then stand, and them ambulate. Client reported eating a small breakfast that morning, and vaccine was given during his normal lunch time at the facility. He had also just come from a stressful meeting.
PATIENT HAD SEIZURE ABOUT 10MIN AFTER RECEIVING VACCINE WHILE SITTING IN THE WAITING ROOM

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Had migraine for the 1st 3 days following the vaccine. Over the next couple of weeks became "mentally foggy and fatigued". When he came to me for a first aid/vital sign check at the occupational clinic, I observed that both of his hands were trembling and did not appear to feel well. I asked that he leave and follow up with his PCP and obtain a full medical release to return to work. He has returned back to work this week and informed me of the events /reaction that he attributes to the vaccine. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Two days after I received vaccine I woke up in middle of night and I developed a hematoma it was the size a baseball, it was the color of a lobster it was an inch below the injection site. It took almost 2-3 weeks to go away and then when it went down, I developed shingles anterior side of my elbow. I was in vacation when the shingles started and I broke out from head to toe in hives. When I got back I went to the doctors . The doctor said it was too late for medication and it needed to run its course. I started having left flank pain on April 30th, I woke up with severe flank pain. On May 7th I saw the doctor again, she was surprised that shingles had not gone away. The shingles started in my arm internally into my kidney . I lost all feeling in my left abdomen . The doctor thought i had a UTI and she gave me medicine for UTI , the test came back I didn't have a UTI. On May 12 They did an ultrasound of my left quadrant . On May 14th I went back to doctor I was still having a rash. On May 16th I went to the ER. They did every test you could imagine because I was in such pain. They could not find anything sent me home with Pain meds and referred me to gastrologist, He did a colonoscopy and that was normal. Then I developed  a rash over my kidney  , and the pain started to decrease.
LAB_DATA: EKG, MRI, CT Scans, echocardiogram, blood work

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On Saturday, September 4, 2021, at 3:00pm, I left work and went outside to my car. I noticed that everything seemed really bright. Almost whitewashed. Enough that I felt uncomfortable driving. Then about 10 minutes later,  I started feeling a tingling sensation on my right palm. The tingling crept up my fingers and into my finger tips. After a minute or so, my finger tips on my right hand went completely numb. Then I noticed the same tingling  feeling start on my lower lip and quickly, it too went numb. I called 911 knowing that something wasn't right. It was then that I lost all ability to say the words my brain was trying to say. Random words were coming out and then I starting forgetting worlds altogether. Easy things like what I had eaten for lunch or where I was parked was impossible for me to answer. I just couldn't remember the names. By the time the paramedics came to me, the tingling was gone and my brain to mouth connection was back but my memory was still really bad. That is when I started getting a headache. The headache lasts for about 4 hours or so.
LAB_DATA: CT scan, blood work, chest X-ray (these were all taken 2 days after the incident) since I was scared the day of and just wanted to go home.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: First one was pain in my jaw and chest - shortness of breath and elevated heart rate. I went to ER and I was hospitalized for four days and then discharged.  Was monitored while I was at the hospital but no procedures were done. I got IV fluids the first day of it.  They sent me home with what I had already been on before the vaccine. When I was discharged, I was not having those symptoms. I was wearing a 30 day event monitor when I was discharged.  Second health event: Afib episode - June 15 or 16. Went to ER at Hospital - they gave me some different meds this time - Heparin by injection in the abdomen; Increased Lopressor; no fluids or oxygen that time; I was released with new meds - stopped taking Lopressor and Plavix; started on Eliquis and Cardizem and Toprol.  #3 - I was in the hospital a third time - a couple of weeks later on July 14th - shortness of breath and that was the main symptom. They did a chest x-ray in the ER which showed fluids around my lungs and around my heart. They also did a CT scan which verified the same thing. They admitted me and gave me Lasix through the IV for three days. I was there for week that time. Medications stayed the same from after the second time in the hospital when I was sent home. I also had oxygen for a couple of days because my pulse OX rate was dropping and going up and down. They were trying to get rid of as much fluid as possible. They did another echo-cardiogram - was normal as far as heart function.  Doctor appts - have had - cardiologist, pulmonologist and family physician
LAB_DATA: 1st time - Tests: bloodwork; stress test and echo-cardiogram - those were all normal -  2nd time: Did a chest x-ray - mostly monitoring and trying the heart rate to come down which took awhile. I was admitted for two days.  3rd time: chest xray; echo cardiogram

Within 48hrs of receiving the vaccine, I experienced severe joint pain in limb joints, ribs, and back, and noticed a sharp decrease in stamina and a sharp increase in heart and respiration rate upon mild exertion. The severe joint pain consisted of achy, throbbing pain and stiffness with movement, in between and along the bones of the affected joint. This continued for two weeks before dulling away, except in joints with previous injuries, where pain has dulled to a moderate-severe flare up and has not resolved. Breathing became more troublesome, I struggled to take a deep breath or hold a breath, walk more than a flight of stairs before becoming winded, or talk long without running out of air. Chest muscles become easily fatigued and achy, and I sometimes experience lancing pain through my chest and lungs while trying to breath deeply, especially after exertion. Nebulizer treatments, inhalers, and steroids do not help for more than an hour or two before the shortness of breath return. The issue has not been resolved but referred to cardiology and pulmonology.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I came home and I was feeling very dizzy. I have been having to watch my blood pressure very closely. I was pretty nauseated. I checked my BP and it was 88/44. My systolic number is more troublesome than the dystolic. I was shocked with my BP going that low. It was very unstable. I had to go to the doctor because I didn't want to take my medication with my BP being so low. We have been trying for the last week or so to take half of a tablet in the morning and half at night. It's not controlling my higher blood pressure. I took my meds and it seems to have stabilized. Today is looking really good. I just have to be very careful. My BP is still unstable. I normally have very high BP at the dentist and it was really low. It was 95/52. It did shoot back up after about half an hour. I have never had any of these issues prior to my vaccination. The drop happened within 4 hours after receiving the vaccine.

LAB_DATA: 8/11/21 went to the ER, Covid-19 test was negative.  They took 7 vials of blood, EKG, chest x-ray.  Chest x-ray and EKG came back normal.  Troponin level was very slightly elevated.  Blood tests determined that my kidneys were not functioning properly (they called it renal insufficiency).  ER sent me home and told me there was nothing more they could do for me and that my body would either step up and fight it off or not.  The next 4 days I got worse, and then finally started to slowly come out of it.  I was referred to a cardiologist.  I finally got in to the cardiologist on 8-25-21. The cardiologist put me on a heart monitor for 2 weeks.  I just took it off on 9/8/21 and those results are still pending.  The cardiologist did another series of blood tests and determined that my kidneys were functioning again normally.  The cardiologist did an ultrasound (echo) on my heart and determined that there was no permanent damage but I had acute myocarditis and the inflammation may take up to 3 months to fully heal.  Both the ER doctor and the cardiologist both told me that I should not get any more Covid-19 vaccination shots.  I am now a month from the vaccine shot and I still have balance issues and fatigue issues.  I have been off of work since 8/11/21 and cannot go back until the cardiologist gives me the all clear.

Patient presented for COVID-19 vaccination today.  She reported that she has struggled with significant anxiety, with a marked increase in sxs and episodes of profound anxiety within the past years. She noted that anything she ?puts in her body? to include immunizations, and medications may provoke profound episodes of anxiety.  She denied any history of suspected adverse reactions to vaccines, but reported significant concern that she would have marked anxiety in association with the COVID-19 vaccine.  I discussed the vaccine with the patient, and encouraged her to have something to eat and drink prior to vaccination.  Offered option of deferring vaccination on the lanai and choosing a different time/place of her comfort for vaccination.  The patient obtained lunch and returned with desire to proceed with vaccination.   We discussed a plan for a conservative 30min observation period post-vaccination.   Immediately upon vaccination, the patient's administering team noted the patient to be visibly shaking. She reported feeling unwell/dizzy.  She reported tongue numbness, indigestion, GI upset and feeling anxious.  She noted that her symptoms were consistent with prior episodes of marked anxiety.  She was provided a glass of water and an ice pack to her neck.  The  team obtained serial VS, which were notable for BPs in the 140s/80s and HRs in the 80s-90s.    The patient was speaking easily in full sentences, and seemed to relax when distracted with conversation about her move to HI from WA, her children, and her Son?s planned Birthday party.  When not distracted with other topics, the patient expressed concern about her sxs, with corresponding increases in jittering/shaking of her legs.   At patient request, the vaccination team phoned her Husband, who joined the patient .  Upon her Husband?s arrival, I asked him if he had observed the patient look and feel similarly to her symptoms on the lanai.  He reported that indeed, he had been with the patient experiencing the same sxs ?on many occasions?.  He immediately felt the patient?s radial pulse, and noted that her appearance and sxs were consistent with prior episodes of anxiety.    The patient expressed that with prior similar episodes, her Husband?s support and talking have helped to speed resolution of sxs.   She notably had no ocular sxs, nasal sxs, oral sxs, throat sxs, difficulty breathing, or dermatologic sxs.  My colleague and I had assessed the patient prior to her Husband?s arrival. Soon after the patient?s Husband?s arrival, I needed to attend a meeting, and therefore my colleague assumed care for the patient.   Upon my return to the vaccine site approx 45min after my departure, I learned that the patient had markedly improved once her Husband had arrived. After symptom improvement, the patient and her spouse had walked around the vaccine site, walked within the A/C building, and spoke with the vaccine team prior to departing the area.  My colleague obtained VS prior to releasing the patient and patient departure at 1242: HR 149/88, HR 85, Sao2 100% on RA

ENT - Looked at the MRI and said there was swelling in my nasal mucous = and he thought that was the cause of the migraine - especially because I'm getting them in the morning after lying down all night.
